#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the default skin, the sprites are flags, infantry, cavalry and cannon. "
"Infantry represents one army, five for cavalry and ten for cannons. Cannons "
"are also used to display fighting armies. That's why there is three kinds of "
"cannon sprites: normal static or moving cannon, firing one and exploding one."
msgstr ""
"Na aparencia predeterminada os gráficos son bandeiras, infantaría, cabalaría "
"e canóns. A infantaría representa un exército, cinco de cabalaría e dez de "
"canóns. Os canóns tamén se usan para amosar exércitos na batalla. Por iso "
"existen tres tipos de gráficos de canóns: canón normal estático ou en "
"movemento, disparando e estourando."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:410
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Each sprite image is the concatenation of the various views of the object "
#| "and for each view, its frames. Views are organized vertically and frames "
#| "horizontally. Where to cut the image in individual frames is found by "
#| "dividing the height of the image by the number of views and the width by "
#| "the number of frames. These data are found in the onu.desktop file."
msgid ""
"Each sprite image is the concatenation of the various views of the object "
"and for each view, its frames. Views are organized vertically and frames "
"horizontally. Where to cut the image in individual frames is found by "
"dividing the height of the image by the number of views and the width by the "
"number of frames. These data are found in the <filename>onu.desktop</"
"filename> file."
msgstr ""
"Cada imaxe de gráfico é a concatenación das diversas vistas do obxecto e "
"para cada vista, os seus fotogramas. As vistas están organizadas "
"verticalmente e os fotogramas horizontalmente. Onde hai que recortar a imaxe "
"nos fotogramas individuais sábese dividindo a altura da imaxe polo número de "
"vistas e a anchura polo número de fotogramas. Este datos atópanse no "
"ficheiro onu.desktop."

