#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:506
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "This is a png file representing also the map of the skins's world, but "
#| "with coded colors that allows one to identify uniquely each country. "
#| "Countries must have at least the same shapes as the corresponding "
#| "countries on the map.png file so that users can click anywhere in a "
#| "viewable country and select the good one. Countries, like little islands "
#| "as Indonesia in the default map can be greater than the equivalent in the "
#| "map.png file to facilitate the selection of the country."
msgid ""
"This is a png file representing also the map of the skins's world, but with "
"coded colors that allows one to identify uniquely each country. Countries "
"must have at least the same shapes as the corresponding countries on the "
"<filename>map.png</filename> file so that users can click anywhere in a "
"viewable country and select the good one. Countries, like little islands as "
"Indonesia in the default map can be greater than the equivalent in the "
"<filename>map.png</filename> file to facilitate the selection of the country."
msgstr ""
"Este é un ficheiro png que representa tamén o mapa mundi da aparencia, pero "
"con cores codificadas que permiten identificar univocamente cada país. Os "
"países deben ter cando menos as mesmas formas que os países correspondentes "
"do ficheiro map.png para que os usuarios poidan premer calquera parte dun "
"país visíbel e escoller o correcto. Os países, como as illas pequenas como "
"Indonesia do mapa predeterminado poden ser maiores que os equivalentes no "
"ficheiro map.png para facilitar a escolla do país."

